data.meta_description: Need Woodburn demographics? Get current population, race, age, income & poverty statistics for Woodburn, VA from the US Census Bureau.
data.text:
Sources: United States Census Bureau. 2022 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates. U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey Office. Web. 7 December 2023.

United States Census Bureau. Annual Estimates of the Resident Population: April 1, 2020 to July 1, 2023. U.S. Census Bureau, Population Division. Web. May 2024. http://www.census.gov/.

United States Census Bureau. Annual Estimates of the Resident Population: April 1, 2010 to July 1, 2019. U.S. Census Bureau, Population Division. Web. May 2021. http://www.census.gov/.

United States Census Bureau. "P2 Hispanic or Latino, and Not Hispanic or Latino by Race." 2020 Census State Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171) Summary File. U.S. Census Bureau, 2020 Census. Web. 12 August 2021. https://www.census.gov/.

Check out our FAQs for more details.

Population

With 9,960 people, Woodburn is the 129th most populated city in the state of Virginia out of 666 cities. But watch out, Woodburn, because Belmont with 9,888 people and Independent Hill with 9,858 people are right behind you.

Race & Ethnicity

The largest Woodburn racial/ethnic groups are White (51.6%) followed by Asian (29.5%) and Hispanic (9.3%).

Median Income

In 2022, the median household income of Woodburn households was $127,406. Woodburn households made slightly more than Greenbriar households ($127,100) and Occoquan households ($126,927) . However, 9.2% of Woodburn families live in poverty.

Median Age

The median age for Woodburn residents is 32.6 years young.
